description: The Georgia Bulldogs (7-5) and TCU Horned Frogs (6-6) meet in the 2016 Liberty Bowl on Dec. 30, 2016, in Memphis, Tenn.
title: 2016 Liberty Bowl, Georgia vs. TCU
title_page: Photos: 2016 Liberty Bowl, Georgia vs. TCU
text:

Michael Chang/Getty Images Georgia head coach Kirby Smart lifts the Liberty Bowl Trophy after the Bulldogs rallied to beat the TCU Horned Frogs, 31-23, at the Liberty Bowl Friday, Dec. 30, 2016, at the Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium in Memphis, Tenn.

Michael Chang/Getty Images Georgia head coach Kirby Smart laughs after handing the Liberty Bowl Trophy to his players after they defeated the TCU Horned Frogs, 31-23, at the Liberty Bowl Friday, Dec. 30, 2016, in Memphis, Tenn.

Michael Chang/Getty Images TCU wide receiver John Diarse holds on the ball to secure a touchdown in front of Georgia cornerback Deandre Baker in the second half of the Liberty Bowl Friday, Dec. 30, 2016, in Memphis, Tenn. The Bulldogs defeated the Frogs, 31-23.

Mark Weber/AP TCU quarterback Kenny Hill (7) watches a fumbled ball bounce away against the Georgia defense during the second quarter of the Liberty Bowl Friday, Dec. 30, 2016, in Memphis, Tenn. Georgia rallied for a 31-23 win at Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium.

Mark Weber/AP Georgia quarterback Jacob Eason makes a throw against TCU during the first quarter of the Liberty Bowl Friday, Dec. 30, 2016, in Memphis, Tenn. Georgia' freshman quarterback completed 12 of 21 passes for 164 yards and 2 touchdowns.

Michael Chang/Getty Images Georgia wide receiver Isaiah McKenzie runs the ball downfield past TCU safety Ridwan Issahaku at the Liberty Bowl Dec. 30, 2016, in Memphis, Tenn. The 77-yard catch and run set up a first quarter touchdown by the Bulldogs. TCU led Georgia 16-14 at the half.

Michael Chang/Getty Images Georgia running back Nick Chubb looks to maneuver by TCU linebacker Sammy Douglas at Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium Dec. 30, 2016, in Memphis, Tenn. TCU led Georgia 16-14 at the half.
